{
  "texts": [
    "These baselines include well-established models such as Bidirectional Encoder Representations From Transformers (BERT) [30], Embeddings From Language Models (ELMO) [31], and PubMedBERT-Conditional Random Field (PubMedBERT-CRF) [32], which have previously set the standard in clinical NLP tasks.",
    "By comparing the outputs of LLMs against these baselines, we aim to offer a clear perspective on the advancements LLMs represent in the field.",
    "This comparative analysis is crucial for appreciating the extent to which prompt engineering techniques can leverage the inherent capabilities of LLMs, marking a significant evolution from traditional approaches to more dynamic and contextually aware methodologies in clinical NLP.",
    "Prompt Creation ProcessA rigorous process was followed to create suitable prompts for each task.",
    "These prompts were carefully crafted to match the specific context and objectives of each task."
  ]
}